He fired a second shot as they got closer and they reared away.
He was very upset at the situation and felt that they were a danger to both people and animals/pets.
Later that week, people camped nearby observed several wolves and pups resting in the shade under and around Don's trailer.
At the time, he was inside watching golf with his dog, unaware that the wolves were outside.
He was irrate when he learned of the incident, stating that this was not the behavior of wild animals and concerned about what would have happened had he or his dog come out of the trailer.
